### ========================================
### Example 6: Compare endpoints - all articles vs only discounted articles
### ========================================

# This endpoint shows ALL articles with their prices
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/articles?date=2026-06-15&withPrices=true
Accept: application/json

###

# This endpoint shows ONLY articles that have an active discount
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/articles?date=2026-06-15&discountOnly=true
Accept: application/json

### ========================================
### Example 7: Create article with discount that would go below net price
### ========================================

POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/articles
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Article",
  "slogan": "Test",
  "netPrice": 100.00,
  "salesPrice": 110.00,
  "vatRatio": 0.19,
  "discounts": [
    {
      "description": "Big Discount",
      "discountPercentage": 15,
      "startDate": "2026-05-01",
      "endDate": "2026-05-31"
    }
  ]
}

### Discounted price would be: 110 - (110 * 0.15) = 93.50 < 100 (net price)
### This will FAIL with 400 Bad Request

###

# After fixing the discount to be valid:
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/articles
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Test Article",
  "slogan": "Test",
  "netPrice": 100.00,
  "salesPrice": 150.00,
  "vatRatio": 0.19,
  "discounts": [
    {
      "description": "Safe Discount",
      "discountPercentage": 15,
      "startDate": "2026-05-01",
      "endDate": "2026-05-31"
    }
  ]
}

### Discounted price: 150 - (150 * 0.15) = 127.50 >= 100 âœ“

###

# Then check the price
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/articles?date=2026-05-15&withPrices=true
Accept: application/json

